    • isValid

      public boolean isValid(EditAppointmentModel.ValidationParameters validationParameters)
      Performs a series of checks to ensure that the data in the mode is valid. In order, these checks are:
      1. No fields are empty
      2. The end datetime is not before the start datetime.
      3. The start and end datetimes do not fall outside of business hours.
      4. The chosen appointment does not overlap any other appointments assigned to the selected customer.
      5. The chosen appointment does not overlap any other appointments assigned to the selected contact.
      Once these checks have been performed, it returns a boolean stating whether the check was successful. If the check was not successful, then a list of reasons for why it wasn't successful can be found using the getInvalidReasons() getInvalidReasons} method. This method has 2 inline lambdas to help shorten the code and decrease the cognitive load of reading it. One lambda is a forEach lambda used to loop through the appointments assigned to the selected customer. And the other one is exactly the same, only it loops through the appointments assigned to the selected contact.
